schemeContent.benefits_md:
1. Financial assistance of up to 95% of the project cost for income-generating activities, subject to a maximum project cost of ₹50,00,000/-.
1. The beneficiary is required to contribute:

  - 2% of the project cost for projects up to ₹5,00,000/-;
  - 3% for projects above ₹5,00,000/- and up to ₹10,00,000/-;
  - 5% for projects above ₹10,00,000/-.

1. Beneficiaries living below the poverty line may receive a subsidy of ₹10,000/- or 50% of the unit cost, whichever is less.
1. Interest rates payable by beneficiaries are:

  - 6% per annum for loans up to ₹5,00,000/-;
  - 8% per annum for loans above ₹5,00,000/- and up to ₹10,00,000/-;
  - 9% per annum for loans above ₹10,00,000/- and up to ₹50,00,000/-.


> **Mode of Disbursement:** Through State Channelizing Agencies, Regional Rural Banks, Public Sector Banks, and other channelizing agencies associated with NSFDC.

